# Optimized Time Management System in C++

Improved version of a time management system in C++, focusing on code refinement, modular design and maintainability.

## Improvements Over Previous Version (v2)

- Refined class implementation with cleaner logic
- Improved modular structure and file organization
- More readable and maintainable code
- Enhanced utility functions
- Better separation of concerns
- Increased robustness in time handling operations

## Features

- Custom class for time representation (hours, minutes, seconds)
- Time manipulation and formatting
- Modular architecture (`.cpp` and `.h`)
- Utility functions for processing
- Memory management support

## Project Structure

- `practica4.cpp` → Main program
- `CHora.cpp` → Time class implementation
- `CHora.h` → Time class definition
- `utils.cpp` → Helper functions
- `utils.h` → Utility declarations
- `MemoryManager.h` → Memory management utilities

## Concepts Covered

- Advanced Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
- Code refinement and iterative improvement
- Modular programming in C++
- Encapsulation and abstraction
- Software maintainability and readability

## Technologies

- C++
- Standard Library
